    heading Tired of inefficient API security testing?
        strong
    StaticText Automating API security can be a real challenge with tools that take time to set up and offer only a partial coverage.
    heading Lengthy Deployment with Traditional Solutions
    image, url='https://cdn.prod.website-files.com/653f800ead95abddab588b44/66290618e781633f156f2f23_shadow-it-icon%20(1).png'
    StaticText Traditional API discovery and security solutions rely on monitoring API traffic via agents, API Gateways, or proxies, requiring lengthy deployments and leaving shadow APIs—those outside these systems—unnoticed. Many of these solutions also charge based on throughput, making them costly for rapidly scaling organizations with billions of API events per day.
    heading Legacy DAST Tools Fall Short for APIs
    image, url='https://cdn.prod.website-files.com/653f800ead95abddab588b44/662907286807d6772a9873eb_sensitive-data-icon%20(1).png'
    StaticText Legacy DAST tools, when applied to API testing, struggle with scaling and provide limited coverage, creating security blind spots. They also face difficulties in adapting to modern application architectures, such as microservices and GraphQL APIs, and lack automated API discovery capabilities.
    heading Lack of Actionable Remediation Strains Developer Relations
    image, url='https://cdn.prod.website-files.com/653f800ead95abddab588b44/6629072c98cd2ecb4b92e24e_compliance-icon%20(1).png'
    StaticText Many of these tools don’t offer clear, actionable remediation, making it hard to engage developers effectively. This results in unresolved, business-critical issues, ultimately weakening your security posture and slowing down response times.

    heading Tired of inefficient API security testing?
        strong
    StaticText Automating API security can be a real challenge with tools that take time to set up and offer only a partial coverage.
    heading Lengthy Deployment with Traditional Solutions
    image, url='https://cdn.prod.website-files.com/653f800ead95abddab588b44/66290618e781633f156f2f23_shadow-it-icon%20(1).png'
    StaticText Traditional API discovery and security solutions rely on monitoring API traffic via agents, API Gateways, or proxies, requiring lengthy deployments and leaving shadow APIs—those outside these systems—unnoticed. Many of these solutions also charge based on throughput, making them costly for rapidly scaling organizations with billions of API events per day.
    heading Legacy DAST Tools Fall Short for APIs
    image, url='https://cdn.prod.website-files.com/653f800ead95abddab588b44/662907286807d6772a9873eb_sensitive-data-icon%20(1).png'
    StaticText Legacy DAST tools, when applied to API testing, struggle with scaling and provide limited coverage, creating security blind spots. They also face difficulties in adapting to modern application architectures, such as microservices and GraphQL APIs, and lack automated API discovery capabilities.
    heading Lack of Actionable Remediation Strains Developer Relations
    image, url='https://cdn.prod.website-files.com/653f800ead95abddab588b44/6629072c98cd2ecb4b92e24e_compliance-icon%20(1).png'
    StaticText Many of these tools don’t offer clear, actionable remediation, making it hard to engage developers effectively. This results in unresolved, business-critical issues, ultimately weakening your security posture and slowing down response times.

    heading Tired of inefficient API security testing?
        strong
    StaticText Automating API security can be a real challenge with tools that take time to set up and offer only a partial coverage.
    heading Lengthy Deployment with Traditional Solutions
    image, url='https://cdn.prod.website-files.com/653f800ead95abddab588b44/66290618e781633f156f2f23_shadow-it-icon%20(1).png'
    StaticText Traditional API discovery and security solutions rely on monitoring API traffic via agents, API Gateways, or proxies, requiring lengthy deployments and leaving shadow APIs—those outside these systems—unnoticed. Many of these solutions also charge based on throughput, making them costly for rapidly scaling organizations with billions of API events per day.
    heading Legacy DAST Tools Fall Short for APIs

    heading Tired of inefficient API security testing?
        strong
    StaticText Automating API security can be a real challenge with tools that take time to set up and offer only a partial coverage.
    heading Lengthy Deployment with Traditional Solutions
    image, url='https://cdn.prod.website-files.com/653f800ead95abddab588b44/66290618e781633f156f2f23_shadow-it-icon%20(1).png'
    StaticText Traditional API discovery and security solutions rely on monitoring API traffic via agents, API Gateways, or proxies, requiring lengthy deployments and leaving shadow APIs—those outside these systems—unnoticed. Many of these solutions also charge based on throughput, making them costly for rapidly scaling organizations with billions of API events per day.
    heading Legacy DAST Tools Fall Short for APIs
    image, url='https://cdn.prod.website-files.com/653f800ead95abddab588b44/662907286807d6772a9873eb_sensitive-data-icon%20(1).png'
    StaticText Legacy DAST tools, when applied to API testing, struggle with scaling and provide limited coverage, creating security blind spots. They also face difficulties in adapting to modern application architectures, such as microservices and GraphQL APIs, and lack automated API discovery capabilities.
    heading Lack of Actionable Remediation Strains Developer Relations
    image, url='https://cdn.prod.website-files.com/653f800ead95abddab588b44/6629072c98cd2ecb4b92e24e_compliance-icon%20(1).png'
    StaticText Many of these tools don’t offer clear, actionable remediation, making it hard to engage developers effectively. This results in unresolved, business-critical issues, ultimately weakening your security posture and slowing down response times.

    heading Tired of inefficient API security testing?
        strong
    StaticText Automating API security can be a real challenge with tools that take time to set up and offer only a partial coverage.
    heading Lengthy Deployment with Traditional Solutions
    image, url='https://cdn.prod.website-files.com/653f800ead95abddab588b44/66290618e781633f156f2f23_shadow-it-icon%20(1).png'
    StaticText Traditional API discovery and security solutions rely on monitoring API traffic via agents, API Gateways, or proxies, requiring lengthy deployments and leaving shadow APIs—those outside these systems—unnoticed. Many of these solutions also charge based on throughput, making them costly for rapidly scaling organizations with billions of API events per day.
    heading Legacy DAST Tools Fall Short for APIs
    image, url='https://cdn.prod.website-files.com/653f800ead95abddab588b44/662907286807d6772a9873eb_sensitive-data-icon%20(1).png'
    StaticText Legacy DAST tools, when applied to API testing, struggle with scaling and provide limited coverage, creating security blind spots. They also face difficulties in adapting to modern application architectures, such as microservices and GraphQL APIs, and lack automated API discovery capabilities.
    heading Lack of Actionable Remediation Strains Developer Relations
    image, url='https://cdn.prod.website-files.com/653f800ead95abddab588b44/6629072c98cd2ecb4b92e24e_compliance-icon%20(1).png'
    StaticText Many of these tools don’t offer clear, actionable remediation, making it hard to engage developers effectively. This results in unresolved, business-critical issues, ultimately weakening your security posture and slowing down response times.

    StaticText Automating API security can be a real challenge with tools that take time to set up and offer only a partial coverage.
    heading Lengthy Deployment with Traditional Solutions

    StaticText Traditional API discovery and security solutions rely on monitoring API traffic via agents, API Gateways, or proxies, requiring lengthy deployments and leaving shadow APIs—those outside these systems—unnoticed. Many of these solutions also charge based on throughput, making them costly for rapidly scaling organizations with billions of API events per day.
    heading Legacy DAST Tools Fall Short for APIs
    image, url='https://cdn.prod.website-files.com/653f800ead95abddab588b44/662907286807d6772a9873eb_sensitive-data-icon%20(1).png'
    StaticText Legacy DAST tools, when applied to API testing, struggle with scaling and provide limited coverage, creating security blind spots. They also face difficulties in adapting to modern application architectures, such as microservices and GraphQL APIs, and lack automated API discovery capabilities.
    heading Lack of Actionable Remediation Strains Developer Relations

    StaticText Many of these tools don’t offer clear, actionable remediation, making it hard to engage developers effectively. This results in unresolved, business-critical issues, ultimately weakening your security posture and slowing down response times.
